# How Strong Is Your Password Really?
### Testing a GitHub Password Strength Checker for Beginners

**Author:** Nazir Mohammed  
**Course:** CSN 190 – Cybersecurity Project  
**Semester:** Fall 2024  
**Institution:** Bronx Community College  

---

## Project Overview
This project explores password security by deploying and testing an open-source password strength checker from GitHub. Using a Python-based application powered by the Zxcvbn library, I analyzed common passwords, passphrases, and randomly generated credentials to understand how password strength is evaluated against real-world attack techniques.

---

## Software and Tools Used
- Password Strength Checker (Sharma-IT GitHub Project)
- Python 3
- Zxcvbn Password Strength Estimation Library
- Visual Studio Code
- Git
- GitHub

